## ðŸ” Security Best Practices

- âœ… Never commit `.env` file
- âœ… Use environment variables for secrets
- âœ… Add authentication for production (optional)
- âœ… Enable CORS only for trusted domains
- âœ… Rate limit API endpoints if needed

## ðŸ“Š Monitoring & Logs

View logs in Render dashboard:

1. Go to your service
2. Click "Logs" tab
3. Monitor real-time requests and errors

## ðŸ› Troubleshooting

### Server won't start

- Check `CLAUDE_API_KEY` is set correctly
- Verify Node.js version >= 20.0.0
- Run `npm install` again

### Analysis returns errors

- Verify Claude API key is valid
- Check API quota/limits
- Review Render logs for details

### Cold start is slow

- Normal for Render free tier (30-60s)
- Server stays awake for 15min after request
- Consider paid plan for instant responses

## ðŸ“š Extending the Server

### Add a New Service

1. Create new tool function in `src/index.ts`:

```typescript
async function analyzeTwitterProfile(data: any): Promise<string> {
  const prompt = `Analyze Twitter profile for: ${data.twitter_url}`;
  // ... Claude API call
  return response;
}
```

2. Add to `/api/analyze` endpoint:

```typescript
if (service === 'twitter_branding') {
  const twitterAnalysis = await analyzeTwitterProfile(data);
  // ... include in report
}
```

3. Deploy - Render auto-deploys from GitHub!

